18/04/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- European Integration Minister Ermelinda Meksi announced on Friday (15 April) that the government and the EU sealed an agreement on re-admission of illegal immigrants from Albania into the EU. Meksi said the accords envision taking back individuals -- Albanian nationals and others -- who used Albania's territory to enter the Union illegally. She noted that signing the deal was part of ongoing efforts to speed up the process of EU integration. (Albanian News - 16/04/05; AP - 15/04/05)
